@endnode

@node "Document_2" "Requirements"
@toc "Document_0"
@next "Document_3"
@prev "Document_1"

 @{b}Requirements@{ub}
 @{b}============@{ub}

 - Amiga with AGA Chipset

 - A Multisync Monitor that can display screens with 54 Hz 22 kHz

 - OS 3.x and WB 3.x

 - Free ChipMem.. (A picture in 1024x768 with 8 BitPlanes needs 768KB !)

 - You need the following files on your SYS-partition:


   @{b}UTILITIES/MULTIVIEW@{ub} - to display the demoscreen

   @{b}DEVS:MONITORS@{ub}       - the directory for the monitorfiles

   @{b}PREFS/OVERSCAN@{ub}      - for Installation

   @{b}PREFS/SCREENMODE@{ub}    - for working with HighGFX
@endnode

@node "Document_3" "Installation"
@toc "Document_0"
@next "Document_4"
@prev "Document_2"

 @{b}Installation@{ub}
 @{b}============@{ub}

 If you want to start the automatic installation, click on the
 magic button.

 A little installation script will started and copy the monitorfiles
 to your @{fg shine}DEVS:MONITORS@{fg text} directory.

 After copying the files, the script will install the new modes and
 executes the @{fg shine}PREFS/OVERSCAN@{fg text} tool from your WB.

 Now you @{b}MUST@{ub} choose HighGFX and place the screen in a @{b}visible@{ub} position.
 @{b}@{u}Don´t change the screensize !@{ub}@{uu}

 After this step, @{b}save@{ub} your setup and @{b}cancel@{ub} the WB-requester.

 That´s all.


                           @{"« MAGIC BUTTON »" system "NEWCLI from Install.bat"}
@endnode

