@node "Document_6" "Tested with"
@toc "Document_0"
@next "Document_7"
@prev "Document_5"

 @{b}Tested with@{ub}
 @{b}===========@{ub}

 HighGFX is tested with various programms.

 Here comes a short list of programms, that works fine with HighGFX.


 - Workbench 3.x      This works fine. (Try 1024x384 ...)

 - MagicWB            Great tool, but the icons are better for
                      1024x768 (great if you own a AGA-ScanDoubler)!
                      Or try the new icons for the 1024x384 screen.

 - DPaint             Fantastic .... (Needs a lot of free ChipMem!)

 - PPaint             Fantastic .... (Needs a lot of free ChipMem!)

 - ShapeShifter       Works fine ... (Try 512x384 Mono for real
                                      MacClassic feeling @{b};-)@{ub}   )

 - PC-Task            Works fine ... Now you can display a PC-Screen
                      with a resolution of 1024x768 on a normal
                      AGA-Amiga  (This is real "@{b}SVGA@{ub}"-feeling)!

 - NemacIV            This is very nice ...
                      I have used it in 256x192 on my old EC030-System.
                      This is the fastest fullscreen mode ....
                      Now I own a 060 board and I use 512x384, even
                      very smooth ...
                      Try this new modes ...
@endnode

@node "Document_7" "BUGS"
@toc "Document_0"
@next "Document_8"
@prev "Document_6"

 @{b}BUGS@{ub}
 @{b}====@{ub}

 Known BUGS in this release are:

 - Prefs/Overscan      (Rating: Harmless)
   After first installation you must set your screen-area in
   a visible position

 - MUI-ScreenRequester (Rating: FATAL)
   This version has great problems with MUI
   Use your original WB3.x ScreenmodeRequester instead

 If you found more BUGS (I don´t hope so)
 send me your BUGREPORT !
@endnode

@node "Document_8" "History"
@toc "Document_0"
@next "Document_9"
@prev "Document_7"

 @{b}History@{ub}
 @{b}=======@{ub}

 (40.0)  V0.1 - V0.8  - internal releases only

 (40.1)  V0.9 Beta    - first offical Release
         (AMINET)     - with hard limitations
                        (only 1MB ChipMem possible)
                        and a very nice animation
                      - frequencys: 45Hz 18kHz
                      - MANY MANY BUGREPORTS !! (Urghh ..)

 (40.2)  V0.9 DEMO    - pushed the screen-performance up to:
         (AMINET)       50 Hz 20 kHz (@{b}@{u}10% more !!@{ub}@{uu})
                        Now it´s equal to PAL (50 Frames)
                      - removed the animation and the
                        ChipMem-Limitation
                        (They were the reason for the most
                        bugreports ..... so, they must gone)
                      - now it works 100% with M1438-Monitors
                        (MICROVITEC or AT Types)

 (40.3)  INTERNAL     - internal release
                        50 Hz 20 kHz
                      - corrected the overscan valous
                        no more crashes with to high settings

 (40.4)  AMINET       - pushed the screen-performance up again:
                        @{b}52 Hz 21 kHz@{ub}
                        splitted the archiv in little parts
                        1. driver      (and installation)
                        2. testgfx     (the demoscreen 1024x768 ham8)
                        3. xen-icons   (MWB-Icons for 1024x384)
                        4. patterns    (Backgroundpatterns for MWB+HighGFX)
                        5. screenshots (Screenshots from my WB)

 (40.5)  AMINET       - screen-performance pushed up again:
                        @{b}54 Hz 22 kHz@{ub}
                      - VGAOnly-Bug removed


              - @{u}@{fg shine}IMPORTANT@{uu}@{fg text} this release dosn´t work with
                MUI-ScreenRequesters !!!
@endnode

@node "Document_9" "BonusTool: ReSync"
@toc "Document_0"
@next "Document_10"
@prev "Document_8"

 @{b}BonusTool: ReSync@{ub}
 @{b}=================@{ub}

 ReSync is a tool to fix "scanning" problems on bad MultiSync-Monitors.

 It forces the monitor to switch faster and "better" between two different
 ScreenModes like DblPAL and Productivity.

 Installation: Put the icon in your WBStartup. (That´s all)

 Known Bugs:   Problems if you change between Amiga- and GfxBoards-Modes

 History:      V0.1-V0.8  internal only

               V0.9 BETA  first offical release
@endnode

